EXCHANGER
---------
It enables two threads to swap data at a designated meeting point,
making it useful in various multithreading scenarios.

Key Features of Exchanger:

1)Thread Synchronization: It blocks both threads until they are ready to exchange objects.
2)Object Exchange: Each thread provides an object, and the Exchanger swaps them.
3)Use Cases: Commonly used in producer-consumer patterns, pipeline designs, or scenarios requiring data handoff between threads.